Dear Mr. Adams

I am writing YOU to complain about cellular phone Apple Iphone SE which I HAVE
bought in your on-line shop one month ago.

I am not satisfied with the product and THE service you offer. There are the
FOLLOWING specific reasons. Firstly, you state on your website that the
maximum delivery time for the shipment is five days. Nonetheless, I was
waiting for three weeks. In other words, this is almost four times longer time
than you declare.

Secondly, your advertisement promised that if there were any problems, they
would be resolved very quickly and willingly by your employees. In my case, it
was a completely different reality. The phone broke down JUST AFTER three days
of use. HENCE I decided to call your company. The staff were not pleasant at
all. Moreover, they DID not seem to understand much about the issue.
Ultimately, their advice TURNED TO BE unnecesSary. The phone is still not
working.

I am of the opinion that choosing and communicatING WITH your on-line shop has
been total waste of both my time and money. Therefore, I demand a complete
refund OF THE COSTS, including postage and packing.


Zkusil jsem tam něco vylepšit. Jinak teda ale po obsahové stránce se mi to
nezdá optimální. Je to takový nářek na všechno možné. Reklamace musí být
věcná:

According to the EU act ...., I hereby claim product Apple IPhone SE, sn
123456, which I have bought on your web side xxxxx on DD-MM-YYYY. Despide an
efffort to solve the issue with your service desk on DD-MM-YYYY, the product
still shows the following defects:

a prostě popsat co to dělá. A pak že odstupuješ od smlouvy (pokud to jde) a že
do tehdy a tehdy žádáš vrátit tolik a tolik na ten a ten účet. Nebo že žádáš
výměnu výrobku.

To že ti to dodal později, nebo že na jeho helpdesku sedí kreténi (jako
ostatně na každém helpdesku), to je fuk. Nebo teda "irelevantní", jestli to
chceš po právnicku.
